        "club_bar_guys": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>Mia was lying on the grass, eyes closed. She smiled when you sat down.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>You said you went to a club last week. How was it?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Music was good but the crowd was awful. Still, one guy caught my attention. Sitting alone at the bar while everyone else danced. Just watching.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Did he interest you?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Yeah. Because he was confident. Wasn't trying to impress anyone.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Did you talk?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>I went up to him. 'Why aren't you dancing?' He said 'Waiting for the right song.' That one sentence was enough.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Then what?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>The right song came on. Use your imagination for the rest.<</dialog>>`,
                friendship: 1, trust: 1, love: 0, lust: 1
            }
        ]
    },

    "sunsetPark_common_evening": {

        "guys_slept_with": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>Mia was sitting on a bench, legs stretched out, looking completely at ease.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>Seeing anyone lately? You've been quiet about it.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Seeing someone? There was a guy last week but it was a one-time thing. He didn't call, I didn't call.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Didn't that hurt?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Why would it? We both got what we wanted. Not everything has to turn into a relationship. Sometimes the night is just good, and then it's over.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Being this comfortable about it… I'm a little jealous honestly.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>I'm not comfortable, I'm honest. When you're honest with yourself, you're at ease with others too. Nothing to be ashamed of, we're adults.<</dialog>>

