        ],

        "dilf": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>You noticed Mia watching a man on a nearby bench as she walked through the park. You caught up to her.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>I saw you staring at that guy just now. Do you know him?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Don't know him. But I want to. That beard, that posture… textbook DILF.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>You use that word way too casually.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Because it's real. Young guys are exciting but messy. A mature man knows what he wants.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Have you ever actually been with someone older?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Not yet. But I've thought about it. It'll happen someday. No rush on this one.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>That's the only thing you're patient about, I think.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Some things are worth the wait.<</dialog>>`,
                friendship: 1, trust: 1, love: 0, lust: 1
            }
        ],

        "sugar_daddy_hints": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>Mia was on her phone in the park. A long message was open on the screen.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>Who writes you messages that long?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Someone I know. Inviting me to dinner this weekend. Expensive place.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Someone you know? Is he your age at least?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>No. Older. He paid for my nails and a shopping trip last time. Now he's picking a restaurant I can't even pronounce.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>So what does he want from you?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>He likes spending on someone. That's how he shows interest. I show up, look good, keep him company. That's my end.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Still feels weird to me.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>I get that. But I know where I stand. The second it feels wrong, I'm out. I've always been like that.<</dialog>>`,
                friendship: 1, trust: 1, love: 0, lust: 0
            }
        ],

        "fwb": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>Mia was walking through the park looking cheerful. She hooked her arm through yours when she reached you.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>You're in a good mood. Something happen?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Last night was good. Hung out with a friend.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Which friend?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>You know I have guy friends. With one of them, let's say we did more than watch a movie.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Again? How many of these 'friends' do you have?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Two right now. Both know the rules.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>What rules?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>We don't text each other goodnight, nobody checks in. You want to come, you come. You don't, no problem. Freedom.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>That sounds really cold to me.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>That's not cold. We have a good time every time we hang out. It's warmer than most relationships I've seen. We just skip the fighting part.<</dialog>>`,
                friendship: 1, trust: 1, love: 0, lust: 1
            }
        ],

        "club_bar_guys": [
            {
                text: `<<narrative "Sunset Park">>Mia was sitting on a bench, scrolling through photos on her phone.<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>What are you looking at?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Found last night's guy on Fotogram. Met him at the bar.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>That was fast. How'd you find him?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Mutual friend. Two taps. Profile's public, photos aren't bad… but there are pictures with a girlfriend.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>He has a girlfriend? He didn't tell you?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>Of course he didn't. Had that whole 'I'm single' energy at the bar. Classic move.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "player">>Did you used to trust guys like that?<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>I used to. Not anymore. Now I check the profile first, then decide. Lesson learned.<</dialog>>

<<dialog "neighborMia">>Some guys don't know boundaries. Has anyone ever… done something you didn't want? Touched you or anything?<</dialog>>

<div class="location-actions">
<<btn "Yes, it happened.">>
    <<replace "#miaQ_touch">>
<<dialog "player">>Yeah… it happened once.<</dialog>>
<<dialog "neighborMia">>I'm so sorry. It's not your fault, know that. If you ever want to talk about it, we can. If not, we'll close the subject.<</dialog>>
    <</replace>>
    <<rememberChar "neighborMia" "player_unwanted_touch" "yes" "personal" "Mia asked about unwanted touch">>
<</btn>>
<<btn "No, thankfully not.">>
